        <div class="main-content">
            <div class="part-section">
                <h2>Part I: The Family</h2>
                <h3>Key Events:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Brother John's death devastates family</li>
                    <li>Government agents arrive to take children</li>
                    <li>Grandmother Naomi shares traditional wisdom</li>
                    <li>Family flees into wilderness</li>
                    <li>Saul is eventually captured</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="part-section">
                <h2>Part II: St. Jerome's School</h2>
                <h3>Key Events:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Forced assimilation and cultural suppression</li>
                    <li>Physical, emotional, and sexual abuse</li>
                    <li>Discovery of hockey as escape</li>
                    <li>Mentorship by Father Leboutilier</li>
                    <li>Development of exceptional hockey skills</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="part-section">
                <h2>Part III: The Kellys</h2>
                <h3>Key Events:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Foster placement with loving family</li>
                    <li>Joins the Moose junior hockey team</li>
                    <li>Faces increasing racism at games</li>
                    <li>Becomes standout player despite obstacles</li>
                    <li>Attracts attention from professional scouts</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="part-section">
                <h2>Part IV: Professional Hockey</h2>
                <h3>Key Events:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Recruited to professional team</li>
                    <li>Experiences isolation and pressure</li>
                    <li>Repressed memories surface</li>
                    <li>Reveals truth about Father Leboutilier's abuse</li>
                    <li>Suffers complete breakdown and addiction</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="themes-section">
            <h2>Major Themes</h2>
            <div class="themes-grid">
                <div class="theme-card">
                    <h3>Cultural Genocide</h3>
                    <p>The systematic destruction of Indigenous culture through residential schools, loss of language and traditions, and intergenerational trauma.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="theme-card">
                    <h3>Identity & Belonging</h3>
                    <p>Struggle to maintain Indigenous identity in white-dominated spaces and the challenge of existing between two worlds.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="theme-card">
                    <h3>Racism & Discrimination</h3>
                    <p>Institutional racism in Canadian society, sports as both escape and exposure to racism, and the burden of representation.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="theme-card">
                    <h3>Healing & Resilience</h3>
                    <p>The power of traditional Indigenous healing practices, community support, and the possibility of reclaiming identity.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

